cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.DL. 

The paper describes a system that combines automated theorem provers and machine learning methods to automatically answer mathematical queries. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of machine learning methods for premise selection also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the implementation of sound translations of logic and the integration of advisors with HOL Light, which falls under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and digital libraries (cs.DL).
